usage:
    hop --version
    hop run [--platform <target>] [--arch <name>] [--cache-dir <dir>] [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] <pkgdir|srcfile>
    hop fmt [--check] [<file-or-dir> ...]
    hop compile [--platform <target>] [--arch <name>] [--cache-dir <dir>] [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] <pkgdir|srcfile> [-o <output>]
    hop genpkg[:backend] [--platform <target>] [--arch <name>] [--cache-dir <dir>] [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] <pkgdir|srcfile> [out]
    hop check [--platform <target>] [--arch <name>] [--cache-dir <dir>] [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] [--no-import] <pkgdir|srcfile>
    hop lex [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] <srcfile>
    hop ast [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] <srcfile>
    hop mir [--platform <target>] [--arch <name>] [--cache-dir <dir>] [--diag-format <text|jsonl>] <pkgdir|srcfile>
    hop --version
    hop --help

<target> is one of: cli-libc (default), cli-eval, wasm-min, playbit
`hop run` defaults to cli-eval when --platform is omitted
